                    <h3 class="name">Joyce Hamilton-Whitson</h3>
                    <p>Joyce manages <span class="buisname">A Zappa Dappa Dat's</span> office in Oklahoma and keeps business running smoothly &mdash; but Joyce is also an accomplished musician (a singer and pianist with two published albums), an author (with three novels and counting), <em>and</em> a businesswoman (co-founder of Pinion Records and owner of Hamilton Whitson Studios). Joyce has been involved in the business of music for over ten years, and brings all of her experience and enthusiasm to <span class="buisname">A Zappa Dappa Dat!</span></p>
                    <p>Check out Joyce's albums, <a target="_blank" href="https://www.amazon.com/I-Found-Faith-Joyce-Hamilton-Whitson/dp/B005O4N97I"><em>I Found Faith</em></a> and <a target='_blank' href="https://www.amazon.com/Project-Beautifully-Broken-Joyce-Whitson/dp/B00BTADGO2/ref=sr_1_fkmr0_1?dchild=1&keywords=joyce+hamilton+whitson+india&qid=1591642370&sr=8-1-fkmr0"><em>Project: India 'Beautifully Broken'</em></a>, and her novels, including <a target="_blank" href="https://www.amazon.com/House-Mirrors-J-H-Whitson/dp/1640792384"><em>House of Mirrors</em></a>!</p>
